## Q1 create one directory new at location /mnt
solu:-
ubuntu@ip-172-31-36-28:~$ sudo -i
root@ip-172-31-36-28:~# mkdir /mnt/New
#to check the New directory
root@ip-172-31-36-28:~# cd /mnt
root@ip-172-31-36-28:/mnt# ls
New


## Q2 creat a volume using AWS EBS and attches to your ubantu instance 
step1
1. got to the navigation pane, choose Elastic Block Store, Volumes.
2. click on creat volume 
3. deside  the size of the volume (5gb seleted)
4. make sure that your Availability Zone is same to your instance which you are attching 
5. lastly creat the Volume
step2
1. and go back and selecte your created volume and go to the action 
2. select  attach volume 
3. select your instance
step3
check the output


